SIMPLE: interpreter
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Interpreter
<hw>In*ter"pret*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OF.
<ets>entrepreteur</ets>, L. <ets>interpretator</ets>.]</ety> <def>One
who or that which interprets, explains, or expounds; a translator;
especially, a person who translates orally between two
parties.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We think most men's actions to be the <qex>interpreters</qex> of
their thoughts.</q> <rj><qau>Locke.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Interpretive</ent>⟦br⟧
